bilingual.target: 制定制订颁布 ( 法律或规章 )

bilingual.source: The U.S. Congress has exclusive authority to enact federal legislation.
bilingual.target: 美国国会是唯一有权颁布联邦法律的.

bilingual.source: That's the I of INSPIRE: enact and implement legislation.
bilingual.target: 这是INSPIRE中的I：颁布和执行法律。

bilingual.source: The U. S. Congress has exclusive authority to enact federal legislation.
bilingual.target: 美国国会是唯一有权颁布联邦法律的。

bilingual.source: A law should be amended or repealed only by the same procedures that were used to enact it.
bilingual.target: 法律只有经其颁布之同样程序方能被修正或废除。

bilingual.source: The government has promised to enact legislation, enabling same-sex marriage by the end of the year.
bilingual.target: 政府承诺颁布法律，并在年底前将同性婚姻合法化。

bilingual.source: New York City was the first place to enact a menu-labelling law; it went into effect in March 2008.
bilingual.target: 纽约是颁布菜单标签法的先驱，2008年3月生效。

bilingual.source: For example, a country can enact laws and economic policies to attract foreign investment fairly quickly.
bilingual.target: 例如一个国家可以很快颁布吸引外资的法令和经济政策.

bilingual.source: The parliament voted to enact the proposed bill.
bilingual.target: 议会投票制定了提议的法案。

list.abstract: v.(动词)vt. 制定(法律)；通过(法案) (of the government) make or pass (a law)

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: That means more battles like the one now going on between the Justice Department and California, which <highlight>enacted</highlight> a tough net neutrality law.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这意味着会有更多类似司法部和加利福尼亚州之间的斗争，后者制定了严格的网络中立法。

examination_example.sentence: The key messages that have been put together for World Environment Day do include a call for governments to <highlight>enact</highlight> legislation to curb single-use plastics.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为世界环境日而汇集的关键信息中，的确包括呼吁各国政府制定法规，限制一次性塑料。

examination_example.sentence: This year, it was proposed that the system be changed: Horizon 2020, a new program to be <highlight>enacted</highlight> in 2014, would not have such a category.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 今年，有人提议改变这一制度：将于2014年颁布的新计划“地平线2020”，将不会有这样一个类别。
